description: Under normal market conditions, the Adviser seeks to achieve the fund’s investment objective by investing in the equity securities of U.S. companies in the S&P 500 that the Adviser determines score highly on the Adviser’s proprietary jobs, security and growth (JSG) scoring methodology, while also seeking to outperform the broad equity market. The fund, however, does typically maintain a portion of its assets in cash, typically 1 to 3%.
name: Amberwave Invest USA JSG Fund
